<br>
Now, you are assuming that verant has it's priorities in order. That I completely disagree with. Take Luclin for example. Take the character models, the illusion masks....granted, there will always be bugs, but when you launch a new expansion, and in the first 2 weeks one of the largest selling points of your expansion, i.e. new models, doesnt even work right, you'd think a company with their priorities straight would finish what they started.....we only wish. Instead they launched ahead with another money maker. <br>
<br>
That is the essence of &quot;good&quot; business. They know where the line for most players is for how buggy things get before they get pissed. And they watch that line very closely. Right now, they are willing to let things slid on the &quot;coach&quot; servers because in the end, legends will be bringing in new money. Once legends is up and running, they will have 10x as many buggs running around, and they will have to put all their energy into de-bugging their &quot;first class&quot; customers. <br>
<br>
Not saying that the &quot;coach&quot; servers wont get help, but I think there will be a dramatic increase in how long bugs are let run. All those nice everyother week patches where they modified spells, items, ect.... is going to stop for a while, which some of you will like. Not me. Patches tell me that verant gives a #*%@. It tells me they are trying. <br>
<br>
